#X obj 164 157 loadbang;
#X text 50 16 The example below uses [vline~] to generate an impulse \, which is a single sample with a value of '1' followed by zeros again. We do this by having an immediate jump and then having another immediate jump back to zero delayed by a sample. On the left we use the delay schedule and calculate the delay of one sample in ms. On the right we use [delay] to delay the message by a sample externally., f 56;
#X connect 0 0 4 0;
#X connect 1 0 0 0;
#X connect 2 0 3 0;
#X connect 3 0 0 0;
#X connect 5 0 4 0;
#X connect 5 0 6 0;
#X connect 6 0 2 0;
#X connect 6 1 1 0;
#X connect 7 0 9 0;
#X connect 9 0 8 0;
#X connect 9 0 10 1;
#X connect 10 0 12 0;
#X connect 11 0 10 0;
#X connect 11 0 14 0;
#X connect 12 0 13 0;
#X connect 13 0 14 0;
#X connect 15 0 7 0;
#X restore 278 30 pd impulse;
#X text 128 21 Example on how to generate an impulse, f 19;
#X text 44 76 Example on how to use [vline~] to convert floats to samples with more precision than [sig~], f 31;
